fields.description:
I have created this issue to post the details from my compile errors so that I might be able to receive some technical help

Ingo Muschenetz is looking into this

The project no longer compiles correctly after the 4.1.0GA upgrade, and we urgently need some expert guidance to correct the issues we are seeing.

It is an alloy project, currently just targeting ios, with a number of modules, including 3 which we have authoured to integrate to Healthkit, external accessories, and Bluetooth LE.

Because we are using bluetooth it is necessary to debug on the device as well as use the simulator. 

Also we have been running the app in xcode to debug the native modules.

The project can compile and run on the simulator, but now fails to compile where deploying to a device from appcelerator.

The Titanium iOS build will generate an Entitlements.plist file. If you need to add any additional entitlements, such as for Bluetooth, then:
1) Build your project, preferably for device. If the build fails, it will probably fail after the Entitlements.plist was generated so continue...
2) In your project dir, create the directories: platform/iphone
3) Copy the generated Entitlements.plist file from the build/iphone dir into the platform/iphone directory
4) Update the Entitlements.plist

Then just build the app!

We do not do anything with teams, so that field will be set to "none".

[~mike@warnes.com] Regarding your comment above:

1) I've been talking to another iOS guy about exposing this stuff via the tiapp.xml so you don't need to do this. Until we figure out a solution, you'll have to muck with the SDK's default Xcode project. :(

2) You don't need to do that. In your project directory, create a folder "platform" and inside that create a folder "iphone". Any file you drop in that {{platform/iphone}} directory gets copied during build into the {{build/iphone}} directory. Any files/subdirs in the {{platform/iphone}} directory will overwrite their destination in the build dir, so you need to be a little careful.

3) Not sure why those modules would clash. Perhaps our QE team could investigate.

4) Make sure you name {{Entitlements.plist}} with a capital E.

5) Also make sure you name {{Info.plist}} with a captial I. You could also set the plist settings via the tiapp.xml inside the {{<ios><plist>}} section.
